description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is a fixed term appointment based wholly at Wye Valley NHS Trust County Hospital in Hereford, the successful applicants will join our friendly and enthusiastic education team. This post is designed to support development in medical education for the post-holders through planning and delivering teaching whilst maintaining and progressing with clinical experience within your own specialty (urology). &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will spend half of your role in education; teaching medical students, doctors in training and multidisciplinary teams. Additionally you will be encouraged and financially supported to complete a Postgraduate Certificate in Medical Education (or equivalent credits)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;There is a fully equipped Simulation Suite including the 3G Sim Man, which provides a further dimension to medical teaching in Hereford plus a new multi-professional Clinical Skills and Simulation Academy. The Trust launches an Education Directorate in 2020 which will support and promote shared learning across professional groups. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The constantly evolving and dynamic &lt;strong&gt;urology department&lt;/strong&gt; is a cohesive and harmonious team consisting of four consultants, a deanery appointed SpR, three urology CNS’s and a foundation doctor. A wide range of urological services are offered including oncology, functional urology and stone services. In addition:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is operating potential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Current Urology Fellow 100% NTN success rate, and CEF 90% success rate&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Publication/ presentation potential&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;International and regional research potential (ESWL/TUC/TCC)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information or to arrange an informal visit please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wasim Mahmalji, Consultant Urologist Wasim.Mahmalji@wvt.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel: 01432 355444 x5659&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Or&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
